com.ephesoft.gxt.home.client

Interface BatchListServiceAsync

  • All Superinterfaces:
    DCMARemoteServiceAsync

    public interface BatchListServiceAsync
extends DCMARemoteServiceAsync
    BatchListServiceAsync is a service interface that asynchronously provides data for displaying in a GWT AdvancedTable widget. The implementing class should provide paging, filtering and sorting as this interface specifies. Life-cycle: 1) getColumns() is called by the client to populate the table columns 2) getRowsCount() is called by the client to estimate the number of available records on the server. 3) getRows() is called by the client to display a particular page (a subset of the available data) The client call getRowsCount() and getRows() with the same filter. The implementing class can use database or other back-end as data source. The first table column is used as row identifier (primary key). It can be visible in the table or can be hidden and is passed as row id when a row is selected.
